<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb567652a-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s1132"><num value="1132">§ 1132.</num><heading> Findings</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Congress finds that—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb567652b-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s1132/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> 182 public transportation systems throughout the world have been primary targets of terrorist attacks;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb567652c-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s1132/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> more than 6,000 public transportation agencies operate in the United States;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb567652d-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s1132/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> people use public transportation vehicles 33,000,000 times each day;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb567652e-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s1132/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> the Federal Transit Administration has invested $93,800,000,000 since 1992 for construction and improvements;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb567652f-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s1132/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> the Federal investment in transit security has been insufficient; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb5676530-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s1132/6"><num value="6">(6)</num><content> greater Federal investment in transit security improvements per passenger boarding is necessary to better protect the American people, given transit’s vital importance in creating mobility and promoting our Nation’s economy.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb5676531-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">(<ref href="/us/pl/110/53/tXIV/s1403">Pub. L. 110–53, title XIV, § 1403</ref>, <date date="2007-08-03">Aug. 3, 2007</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/121/401">121 Stat. 401</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
